headline.main: TRADITIONS SEEN AGAINST ISOLATION; G.J. Swope Tells Propeller Club U.S. Has Been Vital Part of Whole World FLAG GOES TO EVERY PORT Ex-Governor of Puerto Rico Says Freedom of Seas Must Be Maintained

lead_paragraph: The traditions of the United States and the recorded progress of the world both reject the idea of isolationism, Guy J. Swope, director of the division of territories and island possessions of the Department of the Interior, declared yesterday at a luncheon meeting of the Propeller Club of the Port of New York.
abstract: resigns as N Y unit pres
